    # game/areas/oldtunnel2.rpy:3957
    old "It’s made of sheets held by thick bars. The pictures impressed on the surface portray fishers and their catch, sea monsters covered with nets, falling harpies, and working diggers. While it’s doubtful it’s made of a material worthy of turning into blades, it’s priceless. \n\nYou look through the keyhole, observing the continuing path and the clear sky with ease, despite the cobwebs. You take a deep breath of fresh air, then put four fingers inside.[custom1] "
